    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>In your Strategy object, u can add a getter :</p>\n\n<pre><code>public double getMarginRatio() {\n  return (this.totalMargin / this.totalRevenue);\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>then, your order by statement will become \"<code>order by st.marginRatio</code>\"</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 411559,
      "reputation" : 3103,
      "user_id" : 784088,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 50,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/PD7AV.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "iamiddy",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/784088/iamiddy"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1432740581,
    "creation_date" : 1432740581,
    "answer_id" : 30486878,
    "question_id" : 30483567,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Yes with nativeQuery</p>\n\n<pre><code>@Query(value = \"select st from STRATEGY st where st.unId= ?1 order by ( st.totalMargin / st.totalRevenue ) desc\", nativeQuery = true)\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 6414100,
      "reputation" : 2321,
      "user_id" : 4972832,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 83,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/937ce95effe1a94fb31f78ae3bc58505?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Pranav MS",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4972832/pranav-ms"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1763410127,
    "creation_date" : 1763410127,
    "answer_id" : 79822734,
    "question_id" : 30483567,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>This happens because <strong>OpenJPA does not support parentheses inside arithmetic expressions in JPQL ORDER BY clauses</strong>, even though Hibernate does.<br />\nSo the JPQL parser stops when it sees <code>(</code>.</p>\n<p>Final working JPQL query</p>\n<pre><code>@Query(&quot;select st from Strategy st \n        where st.unId = ?1 \n        order by st.totalMargin / st.totalRevenue desc&quot;)\nList&lt;Strategy&gt; findByUnId(Long unId);\n</code></pre>\n<p>This parses correctly in OpenJPA and produces the same result.</p>\n<p>Alternatively if you want to use parantheses , you can try like below by using native query.</p>\n<p><strong>native SQL query</strong> allow full SQL syntax, you can enable by mentioning <strong><code>nativeQuery = true</code></strong></p>\n<pre><code>@Query(value = &quot;select * from strategy \n                where un_id = ?1 \n                order by (total_margin / total_revenue) desc&quot;,\n       nativeQuery = true)\nList&lt;Strategy&gt; findByUnId(Long unId);\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
